<h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

<h4>What is Factlink?</h4>
<p>Factlink helps people understand how credible the information is that they’re reading. We’ve built a platform that lets you share what you know by creating Factlinks. By selecting any statement on the web and ‘attaching’ review information like supporting or weakening facts, you can share your knowledge.</p>
<p>Factlink is built on the belief that information should be openly shared, accessible, and transparent.</p>

<h4>How do I create a Factlink?</h4>
<p>This brief screencast will give you an overview on how to use Factlink:</p>
<%= render "home/pages/help/screencast" %>

<h4>On Factlink.com</h4>
<p>The <strong>easiest</strong> way to create a Factlink is by adding on directly to one of you channels. Select the channel you wish to add the Factlink to from the left column on the site. The input field at the top of the channel allows you to type in and post a new Factlink to this channel.</p>

<h4>Everywhere on the web</h4>
<p>The <strong>coolest</strong> way to create a Factlink is by using our browser extension or the Factlink Bookmarklet. These will enable the Factlink annotation mode on any website that you will visit. When enabled, creating a Factlink is as easy as selecting the text you want to Factlink and select your opinion.</p>

<ul style="list-style: disc;">
  <li>The extension is enabled by default. Select your text and click the extension to Factlink.</li>
  <li>Enable the bookmarklet by clicking on it when you are on the page you want to Factlink</li>
</ul>

<p>You can find the extension and Bookmarklet in the <b class="caret" style="margin: 7px 0 0;"></b> menu at the top right of this page.</p>

<%= image_tag('support/chrome-extension-demo.png') %>
<span style="margin: 0 0 0 48px; padding: 0 0 24px; color: #777; display: block; width: 100%; text-align: center;"><super>The extension is available at the top right of your browser.</super></span>

